<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1850-05-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1850-05-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="227" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                            <head><seg type="margin">[671]</seg> *<hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Preston</persName>, Secretary of the Navy, to
                                    Commodore <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, commanding home
                                    squadron.</hi></head>
                            <dateline><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Navy
                                    Department</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1850-05-15"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 15,
                                1850</date>.</dateline>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The confidential instructions, in
                                relation to which I conferred with you this morning, are being
                                prepared, and will be dispatched by to-morrow’s mail.</p>
                            <p>As there is no vessel of the home squadron within your reach, I have
                                not deemed it necessary to order you to proceed to the scene of
                                action, and particularly as the condition of your family is such as
                                to render it somewhat inconvenient to you.</p>
                            <p>The Saranac will proceed forthwith.</p>
                            <p>I am, very respectfully, yours, &amp;c., &amp;c.,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <list>
                                        <item>WILLIAM B. PEESTON.</item>
                                        <item>Commodore <hi rend="smallcaps">F. A.
                                                Parker</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Commanding Home
                                                Squadron, Washington, D. C.</hi></item>
                                    </list>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>